title: Kerala State Junior Men’s Basketball Championship 2022: Quarter-Final Matches and Standings
text:
2023-12-29 00:14:00
Mancheri: 47th Kerala State Junior Men-Junior Basketball Bo The championship quarter-final matches will be held on Friday.
Kottayam, Thrissur, Ernakulam, Kozhikode, Malappu in men’s category Rum, Kasaragod, Thiruvananthapuram, Vanitakalil Kozhikode, Kottayam , Thiruvananthapuram, Thrissur, Ernakulam, Kollam, Kannur, Alappuzha Nniwa confirmed the quarter finals.
Reigning champions Kozhikode are back in the league. Thiruvananthapuram lost to Tat Kottayam (33-55) in the evening. Tum (40-53) lost and finished third in Group A. At the same time Kottayam will continue their undefeated run and Pathanamthi Taye (36-12) will be top of Group A. was
Thrissur vs Malappuram (69-23) in other women’s league matches , Ernakulam-Kollam (68-44) and Wayanad Palakkad (46-30). Sarkot beat Idukki (38-28) and Thiruvananthapuram beat Kozhikode (53-40). Ernakulam and Kottayam continue to lead in men’s standings.
Ernakulam beat Malappurath (71-60) in the late game. defeated Pathanamthitta (58-46) and placed first in Group B. Defending champions Kottayam defeated Alappuzha in Group A. Tutti got their second win. Similarly, Thrissur also defeated Idukki (70-39) and won the gold medal in the same group. 1st win, Kottayam vs Thrissur match toppers in Group A will be decided.
In other league matches Thiruvananthapuram beat Wayanad (42-27) and Kollam Kasargod beat Kannur (61-44) and Kozhikode Pathanamthitta (48-16). He also defeated Nnoor (73-52).
